President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster for the Cahuilla Band of Indians and authorized Federal aid to assist in the recovery efforts from severe storms and flooding that occurred on February 14, 2019. Federal funding will be available to the tribe and certain nonprofit organizations on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, facility repairs, and hazard mitigation measures. Mark Wingate has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.